metadata.name: Last Light
metadata.description:
The last chance to capture the Milky Way core at the end of the season last year, had to take the opportunity to get out and shoot. 

A quick dash up to watch the sunset, followed shortly buy a sliver of a crescent moon, the Milky Way core and Venus shining bright above.

New equipment had me fumbling a little but stoked to walk away with this... Well I actually fell down the stair on the way back to the car, still worth it though.
